summary:
I am living in The Netherlands in the last two years, graduated as an architect from Universidad Santo Tomás - Colombia in 2014, starting in Amarilo S.A.S during the fase of construction. I participated in large scale projects such as the expansion of the El Dorado International Airport in 2015 and the refunisment of a 6,000 m2 school, playing a key role implementing research during development of projects.

 I values projects with research and can communicate with colleagues for exchange solutions. Thanks to different types of projects worked in Colombia, I had been able to participate in all the design processes that have allowed her to create spaces of large scale. I works at her best working in team and been expose where is challenge.
